content.description: Main face left of Condor Corner. Start low and left on face holds, then move into shallow seam on the right. Continue to top on the right side of the wall without using holds on Condor Corner. At the top, continue straight through overhanging rock for 11d, traverse left and use both cracks for 11a.
content.protection: Toprope setup - 2 trees 1 nut. Gear on route is there but sparse - the top crux is well protected.

content.description: Fun finger to hand crack just right of condor corner. This route would be classic, but you can easily bail into condor corner, making it somewhat contrived. Rib on the right is on at the start, then traverse over into finger crack.

A couple of moderate moves, then coil up and reach high for the crux holds.  (Figuring out which crimp to use is part of the crux.)  Somehow get your feet up onto the good foothold, then continue on to the top.
content.protection: Looks mighty thin through the crux ....
content.location: The thin seam just left of "The Joker".

content.description: Easy, except for the hard move.
content.location: In the right hand wall, just right of "Salt Peter" and "Fun One".

content.description:
A fairly direct little line.  You'll end up using the crack less than you expect, because there are several incut rails you can curl your fingers around. 

  And keep your feet outside the niches, or you will make things awkward for yourself!  The biggest foothold is not necessarily the best foothold.

The difficulty depends in part on how fat your fingers and hands are:  I find it too thin for my hands, but a bit rattle-y for my fat fingers. 

  Short but very sustained.
content.protection: 2-3 half inch to one inch pieces.
content.location: Just around the left hand corner, left of "Cosmic".
In the right hand wall, just right of "Salt Peter".

content.description: If you bushwhacked your way to Condor Corner, you may as well get on this.  The crux is about 1/3 to 1/2 of the way up and is well protected.  Watch for loose junk since this route isn't exactly well traveled.
content.protection: Standard rack through #3 camalot should do (#4 possibly)
content.location: The obvious corner to the right of Shooting Star
